{"id":"1511.05417","submitter":"Saibal Ray","authors":"S. Ghosh, Farook Rahaman, B.K. Guha and Saibal Ray","title":"Charged gravastars in higher dimensions","comments":"17 pages, 3 figures","journal-ref":"Physics Letters B 767 (2017) 380","doi":"10.1016/j.physletb.2017.02.014","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.gen-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We explore possibility to find out a new model of gravastars in the extended\n$D$-dimensional Einstein-Maxwell spacetime. The class of solutions as obtained\nby Mazur and Mottola of a neutral gravastar \\cite{Mazur2001,Mazur2004} have\nbeen observed as an alternative to $D$-dimensional versions of the\nSchwarzschild-Tangherlini black hole. To tackle the spherical system in a\nconvenient way we have configured that the gravastar consists of three distinct\nregions with different equations of state as follows: [I] Interior region $0\n\\leq r < r_1$,$\\rho = -p$, [II] Thin shell region $r_1 \\leq r < r_2$,$\\rho =\np$, and [III] Exterior region $r_2 < r$,$\\rho = p =0$. The outer region of this\ngravastar model therefore corresponds to a higher dimensional\nReissner-Nordstr{\\\"o}m black hole. In connection to this junction conditions\nare provided and therefore we have formulated mass and the related Equation of\nState of the gravastar. It has been shown that the model satisfies all the\nrequirements of the physical features. However, overall observational survey of\nthe results also provide probable indication of non-applicability of higher\ndimensional approach for construction of a gravastar with or without charge\nfrom an ordinary $4$-dimensional seed as far as physical ground is concerned.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Nov 2015 14:10:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Mar 2017 10:34:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-02"}
{"id":"1602.08979","submitter":"R K Bisht","authors":"Raj Kishor Bisht","title":"A fuzzy based conceptual framework for career counselling","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Advance Computational Intelligence: An international\n  Journal,(2015), Vol 2, No. 4, 27-35","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.CY","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Career guidance for students, particularly in rural areas is a challenging\nissue in India. In the present era of digitalization, there is a need of an\nautomated system that can analyze a student for his/her capabilities, suggest a\ncareer and provide related information. Keeping in mind the requirement, the\npresent paper is an effort in this direction. In this paper, a fuzzy based\nconceptual framework has been suggested. It has two parts; in the first part a\nstudents will be analyzed for his/her capabilities and in the second part the\navailable courses, job aspects related to their capabilities will be suggested.\nTo analyze a student, marks in various subject in 10+2 standards and vocational\ninterest in different fields have been considered and fuzzy sets have been\nformed. On example basis, fuzzy inference rules have been framed for analyzing\nthe abilities in engineering, medical and hospitality fields only. In second\npart, concept of composition of relations has been used to suggest the related\ncourses and jobs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Nov 2015 09:14:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-01"}
